text: Dalarna County () is a county in central Sweden, with the seat located in Falun. It was established in 1647 as Kopparberg County (), before changing the name in 1997. ==Municipalities== *Avesta *Borlänge *Falun *Gagnef *Hedemora *Leksand *Ludvika *Malung-Sälen *Mora *Orsa *Rättvik *Smedjebacken *Säter *Vansbro *Älvdalen == References == ==Other websites== Category:1647 establishments in Europe Category:Dalarna County Category:17th-century establishments in Sweden
